author: NEW YORK DAILY NEWS
title: Prince Carl Philip of Sweden and Princess Sofia expecting
text:
Mikael Fritzon/AP Prince Carl Philip sitting with his bride, Sofia Hellqvist in a carriage, after their wedding ceremony in Stockholm. A royal bundle is on its way.
Prince Carl Philip of Sweden and wife Princess Sofia are expecting their first child.
The royal couple announced the baby news on Facebook, along with a black-and-white photo of themselves. Princess Sofia's due date is April 2016. The newborn will be fifth in line to succession to the Swedish throne, People reports.
"We are so happy and excited to announce that we are expecting our first child," the said in a joint statement. "We are very much looking forward to it."
Kungahuset.se via Facebook Prince Carl Philip and Princess Sofia are expecting their first child. The stunning pair wed in June in a lavish wedding held at the Royal Chapel in Stockholm.
Before her crowning royal moment, Princess Sofia was a former reality star and model.
She’s not in bad company: sister-in-law Crown Princess Victoria is also expecting a baby next year.
